The paper analyzes a game theoretic problem related to the security of open distributed systems, specifically the Bitcoin digital currency. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including game theory (cs.GT), cryptography and security (cs.CR), distributed computing (cs.DC), complex systems (cs.CY), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Among these, cs.GT and cs.CR are the most likely categories, as the paper explicitly discusses game theory and security issues.
